  "texts": [
    "This model performs well, however it requires carefully placed cameras and struggles with new poses.",
    "MonoHuman (Yu et al. 2023) overcomes this by using a shared bidirectional deformation modules that disentangles forward and backward deformation into rigid skeletal motion and non-rigid motion.",
    "Forward deformation regards the transformation from canonical space to a unique observation space, while backward deformation accomplishes the opposite.",
    "To guide training for new poses, forward correspondence features at known key frames are selected from an observation bank and visual features are evaluated relative to the features in the new observation space.",
    "This improves volumetric consistency between different observation spaces, meaning sequences of actions can be recovered with more 1 3 confidence."
  ],
